    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-01-15T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-01-15T13:00:00-05:00" n="619"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d619">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">816.00 Revolutions/56: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Guatemala</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WS1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Whitehouse</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-01-15T11:00:00-07:00"
                            >January 15, 1932—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 2:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3. My 1, January 5, noon. Minister for Foreign Affairs sent for me this morning
                    to tell me that agreement will be reached on <persName corresp="#p_GZA1">Gómez
                        Zárate</persName> as successor to <persName corresp="#p_MH1"
                        >Martínez</persName>. The Minister saw <persName corresp="#p_AA3"
                        >Araujo</persName> last night who gave him to understand he would make no
                    difficulties if <persName corresp="#p_MH1">Martínez</persName> would pay him his
                    election expenses to the tune of about $40,000 as <persName corresp="#p_AA3"
                        >Araujo</persName> said he was very hard up. <persName corresp="#p_AA3"
                        >Araujo</persName> has had some hope of armed assistance from Honduras but
                        <persName corresp="#p_SKA1">Skinner Klee</persName> told him that if he
                    tried anything like that they would expel him at once from Guatemala.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Salvador.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WS1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Whitehouse</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
